Text: Welcome to the Facial Emotion Perception Test - MC by Langenecker & Easter. A picture of an animal or a face of a person will appear on each screen. Press space to continue…
For a person, you must choose the facial expression displayed. For an animal, you choose the category of animal that you see. Press space to continue…
You are to keep your right-hand fingers on the following keys: space, j, k, l and ;. Press Space to continue

After every animal or face picture you will see a response screen. Click Space to see examples of these response screens. *You do not need to memorize these responses as they will come up after every picture you see*
What emotion did you see? Your choices for emotions are: Sad angry happpy fearful neutral.  Press Space to continue
What animal did you see? Your choices for animals are: dog, cat, fish, bird, monkey primate. Press Space to continue
A prompt (ANIMALS or FACES) will indicate what is coming next. Press space to continue
When ready, please inform the experimenter who will then press the space bar to begin the task
